t&amp;section=3D3" title=3D"Edit section: Matrix definitions involving tran=
sposition"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</s=
pan></span></div>
<p>A square matrix whose transpose is equal to itself is called a <i><a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Symmetric_matrix" title=3D"Symmetric mat=
rix">symmetric matrix</a></i>; that is, <span class=3D"texhtml"><b>A</b></s=
pan> is symmetric if
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e \mathbf {A} ^{\text{T}}=3D\mathbf {A} .}">
  <semantics>
