-align: -0.505ex; width:11.126ex; height:3.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \m=
athbf {A} ^{\text{T}}=3D-{\overline {\mathbf {A} }}.}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>A square matrix whose transpose is equal to its <a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Inverse_matrix" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Inverse mat=
rix">inverse</a> is called an <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/O=
rthogonal_matrix" title=3D"Orthogonal matrix">orthogonal matrix</a></i>; th=
at is, <span class=3D"texhtml"><b>A</b></span> is orthogonal if
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
