<p>A square complex matrix whose transpose is equal to its conjugate invers=
e is called a <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unitary_matrix" t=
itle=3D"Unitary matrix">unitary matrix</a></i>; that is, <span class=3D"tex=
html"><b>A</b></span> is unitary if
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e \mathbf {A} ^{\text{T}}=3D{\overline {\mathbf {A} ^{-1}}}.}">
  <semantics>
